What are cookies

A cookie= is a small text file that a website saves on your computer or mobile devic= e when you visit the Websites. It is used to uniquely identify web browsers= , track user trends and store information about user preferences. It enable= s the website to remember your actions and preferences (such as login, lang= uage, font size and other display preferences) over a period of time, so yo= u don=E2=80=99t have to keep re-entering them whenever you come back to the= site or browse from one page to another.
